President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Alabama and has ordered federal assistance to support recovery efforts in areas affected by severe storms, straight-line winds, tornadoes, and flooding from February 19 to March 20, 2019. The federal funding will be available to state and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The counties of Cherokee, Colbert, DeKalb, Franklin, Jackson, Lamar, Madison, Marion, Morgan, and Winston are included in the funding. Hazard mitigation measures will also be supported statewide. Gerard M. Stolar has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.